      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOOD ODDS MARIO (6) was prominent early from the tricky draw and did a fair job to be beaten 2.5 lengths into second (24.90) at this track in a Grade 5 over 435m. Makes plenty of appeal. ESCAPING BINDI (8) missed the frame latest when sixth at Warragul (26.85) but scored four back at this track (24.59). Cannot be underestimated. NICKED AGAIN (3) has been in super consistent form, finishing in the minors at his last four runs. Last time finished 2nd over 435m at this track beaten 4.5 lengths (25.05) behind Night Sharid in a Grade 5 on July 1. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to his credit. Likely to be in the finish again. ROYAL PRIDE (7) looks a chance coming off a month layoff.",
